Question: How can I calculate the sum of an array in Java?
Please using this api: Arrays.stream.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Arrays.stream
<<<code>>>: int[] array = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};
int sum = Arrays.stream(array).sum();
<<<explanation>>>: The sum() method of the IntStream class returns the sum of elements in this stream. This is a special case of a reduction. This is a terminal operation.
Question: How can I display a bitmap image in a Java applet?: :I am having a hard time figuring out how to show an Image (or ImageIcon) in a Java applet. The following is my code.  The picture (test.bmp) does exist and is on the D drive but when I run this I get the applet window with nothing in it.  Can somebody tell me what I am missing to make the ImageIcon show?public class Form1 extends JApplet {    ImageIcon i;    public void init(){        i = new ImageIcon("D:\test.bmp");    }    public void paint(Graphics g){        i.paintIcon(this, g, 0, 0);    }}Thanks, Steve.
Please using this api: InputStream.read.
Answer:<<<api>>>: InputStream.read
<<<code>>>: InputStream in = new FileInputStream("test.txt");
int c;
while ((c = in.read()) != -1) {
    System.out.print((char) c);
}
<<<explanation>>>: The read() method of the InputStream class returns the next byte of data from the input stream. This method returns an int value which is the byte read or -1 if the end of the stream has been reached. This is a terminal operation.
